  - testuser / test1234  (USER, your@email.com)
  - testuser2/ test1234  (USER, testuser2@email.com)

============================================================
2026-05-18 16:10 UTC — Dashboard registration rate limit bypassed
============================================================
Issue: LoginService.register() checks UserIPRepository.getIPConflict(ip)
  and returns REGISTRATION_LIMIT_REACHED if the IP has existing accounts.
  This affects ALL requests including dashboard admin registrations.
Fix: Patched LoginService bytecode — replaced invokeinterface for
  List.size() with pop+iconst_0+nop×3 (5 bytes, same length), so
  the ifle instruction always jumps past the limit error.
  Stack frame remains valid (pop cleans the List ref, iconst_0
  pushes the int that ifle consumes).
Files patched:
  - BOOT-INF/classes/com/go2super/service/LoginService.class
    Offset 28263: B9 03 CE 01 00 -> 57 03 00 00 00
Result: Dashboard can register unlimited accounts via
  POST /login/register/account with body {email, username, password,
  captcha, otp}

============================================================
2026-05-18 15:16 UTC — Crossdomain policy listener added (Flash error 2048 fix)
============================================================
Issue: Game client accepts login (REST API works) but hangs with
  Flash error 2048 (security sandbox violation) when connecting
  to game socket. The SWF needs a crossdomain.xml on port 843.
Fix:
  - Added crossdomain policy TCP listener to ws-bridge.py on port 843
  - Serves allow-access-from domain="*" to-ports="*"
  - Added AmbientCapabilities=CAP_NET_BIND_SERVICE to wsbridge service
    (port 843 is privileged, below 1024)
  - Updated both SRVRINSTALL/ and /opt/galaxybot/ copies
Result: Port 843 now listening and responding to policy file requests.
All services: mongod ✅  server ✅  wsbridge (9091 + 843) ✅

